[Sadly, the spring of 2022 saw the arrival of highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) and the virus has plagued the northern hemisphere for the year. The fall migration seems to be dragging this virus with it as the wild avian migrate to a warmer climate for the winter. Hopefully, this virus will die out or our birds will develop immunity to this particular strain. May 2023 be better to all of us, especially the poultry owners and operators, and most especially to our birds. - Mod.TG

